title: Which English letters are not present in their own spelling? - Quora

response.answer_text: It mostly depends on how you spell the names of the letters as there are a number of legitimate variations. But there are some letters which occur in fewer of their own spellings: C as ‘See'G as ‘Jee'I as ‘Aye', and ‘Eye'K as ‘Cay'Q as ‘Cue' and ‘Kew'U as ‘Yew'W as ‘Double-u', ‘Double-you', and ‘Double-vee'X as ‘ecks' and ‘eks'Y as ‘Wie'
